@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #EBF4FB
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #2E86AB
skinparam SequenceArrowColor #2E86AB
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #E8F8F5
skinparam NoteBorderColor #1ABC9C
skinparam SequenceDividerBackgroundColor #D5E8D4
skinparam SequenceDividerBorderColor #82B366

title **Phase 1.2 · Séquence — Vues SQL + FE + Enums + Registry**

actor "Dev" as DEV

box "Python Process" #EBF4FB
  participant "phase1_2\n_views_fe" as P2
  participant "CreditScoring\nCleaner" as CSC
  participant "generate\n_enums" as GE
end box

box "Filesystem" #F0FFF4
  participant "data/interim/" as FI
  participant "src/features\n/enums/" as FE
  participant "config/" as FC
end box

box "Services" #FFF8E8
  participant "PostgreSQL\n:5432" as PG
end box

== STEP 0 · Connexion + Vérification ==
DEV -> P2 : python -m phase1_2_views_fe_enum
P2  -> PG : get_engine() + check raw_* tables
PG --> P2 : 8 tables raw_* trouvées ✅

== STEP 2 · Création Vues SQL (cascade) ==
P2  -> CSC : create_all_views()
CSC -> PG  : CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW v_clean_application\n(nettoyage types, valeurs aberrantes)
CSC -> PG  : CREATE VIEW v_agg_bureau\n(agrégat SUM/MEAN/MAX bureau + balance)
CSC -> PG  : CREATE VIEW v_agg_prev_app\n(agrégat candidatures précédentes)
CSC -> PG  : CREATE VIEW v_agg_pos_cash\n(agrégat POS cash balance)
CSC -> PG  : CREATE VIEW v_agg_credit_card\n(agrégat cartes crédit)
CSC -> PG  : CREATE VIEW v_agg_installments\n(agrégat paiements échelonnés)
CSC -> PG  : CREATE VIEW v_master\n(JOIN de toutes les vues agrégées)
CSC -> PG  : CREATE VIEW v_features_engineering\n(FE final : ratios, flags, encodages)
PG --> P2  : 8 vues créées ✅
note right of PG : v_features_engineering = source\nunique pour phases 2, 3, 4

== STEP 3 · Vérification Vue Maîtresse ==
P2  -> PG  : SELECT * FROM v_features_engineering\nWHERE split='train'
PG --> P2  : df_train (~307k × 300+ cols)
P2  -> PG  : SELECT * FROM v_features_engineering\nWHERE split='test'
PG --> P2  : df_test (~48k × 300+ cols)
P2  -> P2  : missing_pct analysis\ntarget distribution\n(défaut ≈ 8%)

== STEP 4 · Export CSV Intermédiaires ==
P2  -> FI  : df_train.to_csv("master_train.csv")
P2  -> FI  : df_test.to_csv("master_test.csv")
note right of FI : Fallback pour phase2\nsi DB non dispo

== STEP 5 · Génération Enums ==
P2  -> GE  : generate_enum_classes(\n  registry=REGISTRY\n  output_dir="src/features/enums"\n)
GE  -> FE  : Écrire ContractTypeEnum.py\nGenderEnum.py\nFlagDocumentEnum.py\n... (1 fichier par domaine)
FE --> P2  : N fichiers .py générés ✅

== STEP 6 · Synchronisation REGISTRY ==
P2  -> FC  : REGISTRY.to_yaml()\n→ config/feature_registry.yaml
P2  -> PG  : REGISTRY.sync_to_db(engine)\nINSERT INTO feature_registry\n(name, type, description, source...)

== Résumé Artefacts ==
note over FI
  **data/interim/**
  master_train.csv  (~307k lignes)
  master_test.csv   (~48k lignes)
end note

note over FE
  **src/features/enums/**
  ContractTypeEnum.py
  GenderEnum.py
  EducationTypeEnum.py
  ...
end note

note over FC
  **config/**
  feature_registry.yaml
end note

note over PG
  **PostgreSQL**
  8 vues créées :
  v_clean_application
  v_agg_bureau / prev / pos / cc / inst
  v_master
  v_features_engineering ← clé
  TABLE : feature_registry (REGISTRY)
end note

DEV <-- P2 : results {\n  train_shape, test_shape\n  db_views: 8\n  enum_files: N\n  t_total\n}

note over DEV
  ⮕  Suite :
  python -m src.pipelines.phase2_feature_engineering
end note

@enduml
